The request body is parsed into ``{{ creds_module }}.{{ creds_name }}``
and passed to ``{{ validate_module }}.{{ validate_name }}``, which
must return a ``{{ session_module }}.{{ session_name }}`` instance on
success or ``None`` on failure.

Token sources: {{ sources | join(", ") }}.  The same JWT is emitted
to every configured source on login and cleared by ``logout``.

Three endpoints are generated:

* ``POST {{ token_url }}`` -- issue a session (login).
* ``GET {{ token_url }}`` -- return the current session as JSON.
  Enforces auth via the shared ``get_session`` dep, so a missing
  or revoked token yields HTTP 401.
* ``POST {{ token_url }}/logout`` -- clear the transport (and
  revoke the server-side record when a
  :class:`ingot.auth.SessionStore` is wired in).
{% if store_name %}

A :class:`ingot.auth.SessionStore` is wired in, so ``logout`` also
calls ``{{ store_name }}.revoke(session)`` before clearing the
cookie.  The revoke runs first so that a failure leaves the token
non-verifying rather than zombie-valid.
{% endif %}

Mount this router in your application::

    from auth.router import router as auth_router
    app.include_router(auth_router)
